PN,30301
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,FThe Bank of England is expected to
OL,8,Fkeep interest rates on hold as
OL,9,Fpolicymakers opt for a cautious
OL,10,Fapproach while assessing the impact of
OL,11,Fwar in the Middle East on the cost of
OL,12,Fliving.
OL,14,FBut experts have said interest rates
OL,15,Fcould increase in the coming months if
OL,16,Fthe conflict continues to put pressure
OL,17,Fon UK inflation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,FMost economists are expecting the
OL,8,FBank's nine-member Monetary Policy
OL,9,FCommittee (MPC) to keep rates at 3.75%
OL,10,Fat the next decision, which will be
OL,11,Fannounced at midday on Thursday.
OL,13,FThe MPC will also publish its first
OL,14,Ffull monetary policy report and set of
OL,15,Feconomic forecasts since the conflict
OL,16,Fbetween US-Israeli and Iranian forces
OL,17,Fbegan in late February.
OL,19,FLast week, figures showed the conflict
OL,20,Fhas helped drive inflation higher.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,FData published by the Office for
OL,8,FNational Statistics (ONS) showed UK
OL,9,FConsumer Prices Index (CPI) inflation
OL,10,Flifted to 3.3% in March, a three-month
OL,11,Fhigh, on the back of increasing fuel
OL,12,Fprices.
OL,14,FThe price of motor fuels jumped by
OL,15,F8.7% month-on-month ` the largest
OL,16,Fincrease since June 2022 ` as
OL,17,Fdisruption to oil production and
OL,18,Ftransportation drove diesel and petrol
OL,19,Fprices higher.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,FMeanwhile, Bank of England research
OL,8,Fsaw UK firms warn they think food
OL,9,Finflation could jump as high as 7% as
OL,10,Fthey increased their inflation outlook
OL,11,Ffor next year.
OL,13,FOther economic data also indicated
OL,14,Fthat activity in the UK economy has
OL,15,Fbeen stronger than expected.
OL,17,FThe ONS reported the UK economy grew
OL,18,Fby 0.5% in February, ahead of
OL,19,Fforecasts of 0.1%, before the conflict
OL,20,Fbegan.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,FElsewhere, UK retail sales volumes
OL,8,Fwere stronger than expected after a
OL,9,Fboost from fuel, with motorists buying
OL,10,Fmore in March in a bid to stock up
OL,11,Famid rising prices.
OL,13,FDespite these figures, economists
OL,14,Fbroadly expect the Bank's rate-setters
OL,15,Fto maintain the current interest rate.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,FOxford Economics chief UK economist
OL,8,FAndrew Goodwin said: "We expect the
OL,9,FMPC to keep bank rate unchanged at
OL,10,F3.75%, with most committee members
OL,11,Fseemingly keen to hold policy at its
OL,12,Fcurrent restrictive level as they
OL,13,Fgather more information about how the
OL,14,Fenergy shock is feeding through to the
OL,15,Feconomy.
OL,26,@pD@VOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,F"Nevertheless, we suspect a minority
OL,8,Fwill opt for a 25 basis point (0.25
OL,9,Fpercentage point) hike, on the basis
OL,10,Fthat some pre-emptive tightening is a
OL,11,Fmore robust strategy to guard against
OL,12,Fan inflation outlook where the risks
OL,13,Fare skewed to the upside."
OL,15,FSandra Horsfield, economist for
OL,16,FInvestec, said: "Whereas military
OL,17,Fstrikes were still underway during the
OL,18,FMPC's last policy discussion, the
OL,19,Fupcoming meeting looks to be held
OL,20,Fwhile the US's indefinite ceasefire is
OL,21,Fin place.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@ZO]xD@QOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,F"However, the repercussions of the
OL,8,Fconflict are still keenly felt and
OL,9,Funcertainty about how the situation
OL,10,Fcould evolve also remains high, which
OL,11,Fwill be key points the MPC will have
OL,12,Fto consider."
OL,14,FElliott Jordan-Doak, senior UK
OL,15,Feconomist at Pantheon Macroeconomics,
OL,16,Fpredicted a unanimous hold vote but
OL,17,Fsuggested recent data could drive
OL,18,Ffuture concerns over elevated
OL,19,Finflation.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777536371
OL,3,CBank of England expected to hold
OL,4,Cinterest rates steady despite
OL,5,Cinflation rise
OL,7,FHe said: "If surveys for May repeat
OL,8,Fthe same pattern, and crucially the
OL,9,F'dirty' Middle East ceasefire
OL,10,Fcontinues with oil flows disrupted, we
OL,11,Fthink the MPC will be bumped into a
OL,12,Fhike in June, or perhaps July.
OL,14,F"We expect rate setters to hike once
OL,15,Fthis year, in June, before cutting
OL,16,Ftwice in 2027 to leave interest rates
OL,17,Fat 3.5%."
OL,26,@oD@JOUvD@AOUyD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
